				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As to the boring debate, sigh, if you dont like healing others then yes this class can be boring, however pumping a fighter down on his Hp full of 300+ hp in one shot is nothing short of a miracle. Being able to sit in the middle of befallen and have no fear is a real thrill. 140+ damage to undead is a great way to garner respect. <BR>
This character class is specialized to a large degree. If you want to wack things be a Monk, if you want to cast damage spells be a mage, If you want to be the most important member in a party be a CLERIC! It takes split second timing, a healthy bit of courage and patience. You cant go up and wack every monster, many will just out damage you. Be a CLERIC! My hints are as follows<BR>
<BR>
1.Most fights that I preside over go are now very similar 1) Early in the fight attack with the fighters trusting in the fact that they will draw the monsters into attacking them, Do you damage early. 2) Wait for the fighters and mages to wear the monsters down then step back and start healing your party. Heal those in great need first then help the others. 3) Hope that the monsters are close to dead because when you start healing 300+ damage a shot the monsters go right for you. HEHE Nerves of Steel I say.<BR>
<BR>

