			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				One: the stun spells for all classes were altered. An early post refers to an 18 second stun for holy might. Its now two seconds.<BR>
<BR>
Two: clerics are 'boring' to people because you spend more time medding than anything else. I watch tv at the same time I play. Staring at the spell book is sensory deprivation to me.<BR>
<BR>
Three: there are cleric specific items. Be patient, they will come to you when you most need them (40+)<BR>
<BR>
four: every class gets some bad spells. deal with it. Eventually veriant will fix them or replace them but for now we suffer.<BR>
<BR>
five: as a dwarvin cleric I am also a tank. But only in the sense that the monsters beat on me. I can easly cast spells with one or two mobs on me if they are not yellow/red. I'm probly the only cleric that is a puller/tank. I enjoy it, and find that using spells wisely keeps me alive.<BR>
<BR>
six: root and holy might line of spells are you god send. root extra mobs before they get to the group. In two spawn situations, I root one and let the second follow. Holy might casts fast enough to get it off when your being beat on. and the 2 second stun is enough time to heal or run.<BR>
<BR>
seven: if you are anything but a dwarvin or human, dont bother with the big ac armors, if there is a piece that will give you wisdom instead. There are two types or clerics, combat and support. You need a high str/sta/agi to be a combat cleric. high elves should always be support clerics.<BR>
<BR>
eight: life begins at 25th level.  Before this there is little to distiguish between the player types except for very specific abilities like SOW or pets. Pretty much any class can kill a white mobs with little help to this point. After this, you have to choose your mobs to be the type you are best at, or group.<BR>
<BR>
nine: the one truth you should all realize is that only about 80% or the early game, and 30% or the late game information is known. People talk about life after 40th very little because the things you see and get are beyond value. The recent fuckup in the fear plane opening underpowered led to alot of poeple escaping with seriously powerful items cheep. They still only got about 10% or whats avalible though.<BR>
<BR>
ten: if you think your stuck and cant progress, consider going back to a ld haunt and getting money for better equipment first, or group with a full group of six. The ep sucks but you do get the nice items.
				</font>
