			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Clerics are the keeper of life within any group. That is your role. Not the big bad DD or grandiose melee artist. I love playing a cleric. The fact that the people depend on me to keep them alive in battle is rewarding enough. The self satisfaction of being all the cleric you can be, buffing , healing, cancel magic, soothing, stunning, wow that is big fun. Especailly cancel magic and stun man those are underutilized. I agree stun is not that great but holy might is very good a very nice amount of time for you to get off a heal or for them to flee. I have a few suggestions and these are only through my expereince. I find myself at my best in group although soloing undead can be a nice break for some extra exp or loot. Depending on our foe, single or mutiple what their con is) I will take to battle and I hit pretty frequently and every bit counts but I will med in a heart beat to protect my group which means heals and I never heal all the way just enough to keep them going and space the heals out because too many in a row and your tanks will be taunting again nothing worse to have to heal yourself what could have been used on your tanks. Do what ever you have to to keep your group alive. if you are trained  and you know you have to run get to the front and attack and yell RUN then cast divine on yourself and let the mobs hit air while your group gets to safety. Cleric is not for everyone, you wont be the big tank that dishes all the damage to that Hill giant and everyone around says he is the man but believe me He knows and everyone in your group knows without those 300 and 600 hp heals he would have been toasted. it is a self glory for you and that is what is great about the class. Some beginning tips, Buy the spells you will need most then follow up later for the ones you could wait on. Always buy healing and buffing spells first, DD and utility later, remember you are not the point man but the support. Buy armor and upgrade as soon as you can, patchwork &gt; leather &gt; banded &gt; plate &gt; rubcite &gt; etc. weapons are not as big of concern for me as is others but I like to have nice ones just not as high a priority as I group alot so I am mostly supporting anyway. <BR>
<BR>
Life can be poor as a cleric so save as much as you can because you are the only class that has to pay for all the high priced spells and buy armor past banded that can really cost.<BR>
<BR>
I want to make one more suggestion as to the class specific weapons. Make a cleric mace 1h blunt 9 damage 37 delay and casts holy might sporadically, woo hoo that would be nice, just something us cleric can call our own.<BR>
<BR>
Rant over
				</font>
			</td>

